OL,3,CMum of man with schizophrenia who
OL,4,Ckilled grandfather say care failings
OL,5,Cpersist
OL,7,FThe cases of Calocane and Barnard are
OL,8,Fsimilar. Both failed to engage with
OL,9,Ftheir health workers and were not
OL,10,Ftaking their medication. They were
OL,11,Fknown to police because of violence to
OL,12,Fothers, and both had families who
OL,13,Fbegged officials to help them and who
OL,14,Fweren't listened to.
OL,16,FAfter many years of treatment, Barnard
OL,17,Fhas now been released which his family
OL,18,Fsay is proof that had he been cared
OL,19,Ffor correctly, the attack on his
OL,20,Fgrandparents could have been prevented.
